# XCF Quick Reference

A concise reference guide for the XCF tool commands.

## Command Usage

After running `use xcf` to activate the tool, you can use simplified commands without the xcf prefix:

```
// Initial activation
use xcf

// Then use simplified commands
current     // instead of xcf current
build       // instead of xcf build
run         // instead of xcf run
lz          // instead of xcf lz (code analyzer)
env         // instead of xcf env
pwd         // instead of xcf pwd
```

## Core Commands

| Command | Purpose | Example | Success Output |
|---------|---------|---------|---------------|
| `use xcf` | Activate xcf | `use xcf` | All xcf systems go! |
| `grant` | Grant permissions | `grant` | Xcode Automation permission has been granted |
| `show` | List projects | `show` | 1. /path/to/project.xcodeproj |
| `open #` | Select project | `open 1` | [No output, selects project] |
| `current` | Show current project | `current` | Current project: /path/to/project.xcodeproj |
| `build` | Build project | `build` | üê¶üìú Built successfully |
| `run` | Run project | `run` | üê¶üìú Ran successfully |
| `analyze` | Analyze Swift code | `analyze file.swift` | # Swift Code Analysis Report... |
| `lz` | Shorthand for analyze | `lz file.swift` | # Swift Code Analysis Report... |
| `env` | Show environment | `env` | Environment Variables: [list of variables] |
| `pwd` | Show current folder | `pwd` | Current folder: /path/to/folder |
| `help` | Show help | `help` | [Lists all commands] |

## MCP Tool Functions

| Function | Parameters | Example |
|----------|------------|---------|
| `mcp_xcf_xcf` | action | `mcp_xcf_xcf(action="build")` |
| `mcp_xcf_list` | random_string | `mcp_xcf_list(random_string="list")` |
| `mcp_xcf_help` | random_string | `mcp_xcf_help(random_string="help")` |
| `mcp_xcf_snippet` | filePath, entireFile, startLine, endLine | `mcp_xcf_snippet(filePath="file.swift", entireFile=true)` |
